Creating a game with HTML, CSS, and JavaScript for the web is a fantastic starting point! I'll break it down into **three phases**: one for the **web-based RPG**, one for turning that game into a **full web game**, and one for turning it into a **cross-platform Android and PC game**. This will give you an idea of how to structure your game from a simple browser-based project to a more complex cross-platform game.

---

### **Phase 1: Web-Based RPG with HTML, CSS, and JavaScript**

In this phase, we'll create a **simple RPG game** with HTML, CSS, and JavaScript. For simplicity, we will focus on creating a basic **battle system**, with a character that can attack enemies, gain experience, and level up.

#### **1. Structure of the Game (HTML)**

The main components of the game would be:

* **Character Stats**: Health, attack power, level, etc.
* **Battle System**: A combat system where the player fights enemies.
* **Progression**: As the player wins battles, they gain experience points and level up.

Here’s the basic HTML structure to get started:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Bury the Light RPG</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
</head>
<body>
    <div class="game-container">
        <h1>Bury the Light RPG</h1>
        
        <div class="character-stats">
            <p id="health">Health: 100</p>
            <p id="attack">Attack: 10</p>
            <p id="level">Level: 1</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="battle-zone">
            <button id="attackButton">Attack Enemy</button>
            <p id="battleStatus">Battle status will appear here.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="enemy-zone">
            <h2>Enemy</h2>
            <p id="enemyHealth">Enemy Health: 50</p>
        </div>
        
        <div id="message"></div>
    </div>

    <script src="game.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
```

#### **2. Styling the Game (CSS)**

You want the game to have a clean, RPG-style look. Here's a basic CSS layout:

